quran[7]{c,v,t,f}:
  61,6,"And [mention] when Jesus, the son of Mary, said, "O Children of Israel, indeed I am the messenger of Allāh to you confirming what came before me of the Torah and bringing good tidings of a messenger to come after me, whose name is Aḥmad."{1} But when he came to them with clear evidences, they said, "This is obvious magic."{2}",footnotes:1:1,footnotes:2:2
  61,7,"And who is more unjust than one who invents about Allāh untruth while he is being invited to Islām. And Allāh does not guide the wrongdoing people."
  61,8,"They want to extinguish the light of Allāh with their mouths, but Allāh will perfect His light, although the disbelievers dislike it."
  61,9,"It is He who sent His Messenger with guidance and the religion of truth to manifest it over all religion, although those who associate others with Allāh dislike it."
  61,10,"O you who have believed, shall I guide you to a transaction that will save you from a painful punishment?"